No Rest for the Wicked is the fifth studio album by Ozzy Osbourne. It was released on October 22, 1988. The album was certified gold in December 1989 and has since gone double platinum. No Rest for the Wicked is the first album to feature Zakk Wylde on guitar. It peaked at number 13 on the Billboard 200
